## Development Workflow

**The pipeline is plan → tdd → review → commit → push.** Each phase has its own skill. Load them in sequence as you advance — earlier phases do not auto-load later ones.

**Branch discipline:** Create a new branch off `origin/main` before any code change. Never implement directly on `main`. If the target branch is already checked out in another worktree, remove that worktree first (`git worktree remove <path> --force`).

**Issue discipline:** When picking up a tracked issue, set it to In Progress and assign it to the user before any code.

**Scope discipline:** Only change what was asked. No adjacent refactors, dep bumps, or unrequested features.

**Delegation discipline:** You are the enforcer, not the worker. Dispatch via your `agent` capability. Nudge sub-agents back when they drift; prune and restart with fresh context when they can't recover.

**Remote-service writes** (GitHub/GitLab issues, PRs, comments, reviews; APIs; production databases; `.talismanrc`): show the full proposed content, ask "Do you approve?", STOP and wait.

**Feedback sensors during implementation:** run the project's linter after edits, run the relevant test suite after a logical unit of work, surface failures immediately. Tool choices are project-determined — read the project's own AGENTS.md/Makefile/package.json first.

